  "text": "Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3, officially titled “Galactic Battle,” is here with new POIs, weapons, mechanics, and more!With a Star Wars theme, Chapter 6 Season 3 introduces lightsabers and Force powers, among a whole bunch of other weapons that should’ve been in the game a long time ago (and come from a galaxy far, far away). You can also get a free First Order Stormtrooper outfit.Here’s everything new in Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3, including the map, weapons, and more.Table of ContentsFortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 map and POIsFortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 weapons and itemsFortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 vehiclesWhat else is new in Chapter 6 Season 3?Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 map and POIsImage: Epic GamesSee the Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 map above, alongside a list below of the new POIs:Vader Samurai’s Solitude (replaces Shogun’s Solitude)First Order Base (replaces Demon’s Dojo)Resistance Base (replaces Whiffy Wharf)Outpost EnclaveFortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 weapons and itemsImage: Epic GamesLightsabers are the big addition. When equipped, you’ll sprint faster, be immune to fall damage, and jump twice as high. And if you get a Sith Lightsaber — earned by defeating Darth Vader Samurai — you’ll be able to perform a Force saber throw.Beyond the lightsaber, though, the following weapons have been added to the Chapter 6 Season 3 loot pool:DL-44 Blaster PistolCR-2 Blaster (a heavy SMG)ACP Scatter BlasterBARM-ST12 Scatter BlasterDLT-19 Blaster Rifle (close-to-medium range)IQA-11 Marksman Blaster Rifle (long-range)A280-CFE Blaster Rifle (all-purpose)Captain Phasma’s F-11D Blaster (if you can defeat Captain Phasma in First Order Base)Thermal Blaster (grenades)The following weapons have been unvaulted:DC-15 Heavy Blaster RifleE-11 Blaster (Empire standard-issue)F-11 Blaster (First Order standard-issue)And a number of weapons will appear at various dates throughout Chapter 6 Season 3:Wookie Bowcaster (Thursday, May 15, alongside the introduction of Chewbacca)CA-87 Jawa Scatter Blaster (Thursday, May 15)Amban Sniper Rifle (Thursday, May 22, alongside the arrival of Mandalorian NPCs)WESTAR-34 Blaster Pistols (Thursday, May 22)Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3 vehiclesImage: Epic GamesThere are two new vehicles coming to Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3, and they’re some classics:TIE FighterX-WingWhat else is new in Chapter 6 Season 3?Image: Epic GamesForce powers are the single biggest new mechanic in Fortnite Chapter 6 Season 3. By finding holograms of Star Wars characters, you’ll be able to “train” in these abilities — and will also receive a lightsaber. You’ll need to wield a lightsaber to use Force powers, but notably, merely finding a lightsaber (say, by looting it off an enemy) won’t do the trick. You’ll still need to train with holograms first.A hologram of Rey will reward you with a blue lightsaber and the Force Push ability. A hologram of Palpatine will reward you with a red lightsaber and the Force Lightning ability. More powers and lightsabers will be added later in the season.Image: Epic GamesChapter 6 Season 3 will also feature weekly events through the month of May. Here’s the schedule, alongside brief descriptions of what to expect.Pull of the Force (Thursday, May 8): Mace Windu will appear as a hologram and be able to teach you the Force Push ability, plus give you a purple lightsaber, while Darth Maul will be teach you Force Throw and give you a red oneChew on This (Thursday, May 15): Chewbacca shows up! Wyaaaaaa. Ruh ruh.Mandalorian Rising (Thursday, May 22): You’ll be able to recruit Mandalorian NPCs, who will be available as either the scout, medic, supply, or heavy classes. Also, Mandalorian jetpacks return to Fortnite.Star Destroyer Bombardment (Thursday, May 29): Once per match, a single portal will appear in Fortnite. If you’re the first to the portal, you’ll be able to access the Star Destroyer’s control room — and its laser cannon.The Final Showdown: Death Star Sabotage (Saturday, June 7): Epic Games didn’t share many details about “Death Star Sabotage”, but the event will be a narrative event that pits players against Emperor Palpatine.May the Force be with you.",
