5/05/fortnite-star-wars-galactic-battle-star-destroyer-1920x1080-70e6f92042d2.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fortnite-star-wars-galactic-battle-star-destroyer-1920x1080-70e6f92042d2.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fortnite-star-wars-galactic-battle-star-destroyer-1920x1080-70e6f92042d2.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fortnite-star-wars-galactic-battle-star-destroyer-1920x1080-70e6f92042d2.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fortnite-star-wars-galactic-battle-star-destroyer-1920x1080-70e6f92042d2.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Epic Games\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eChapter 6 Season 3 will also feature weekly events through the month of May. Here’s the schedule, alongside brief descriptions of what to expect.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePull of the Force\u003c/strong\u003e (Thursday, May 8): Mace Windu will appear as a hologram and be able to teach you the Force Push ability, plus give you a purple lightsaber, while Darth Maul will be teach you Force Throw and give you a red one\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChew on This\u003c/strong\u003e (Thursday, May 15): Chewbacca shows up! Wyaaaaaa. Ruh ruh.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMandalorian Rising\u003c/strong\u003e (Thursday, May 22): You’ll be able to recruit Mandalorian NPCs, who will be available as either the scout, medic, supply, or heavy classes. Also, Mandalorian jetpacks return to \u003cem\u003eFortnite\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStar Destroyer Bombardment\u003c/strong\u003e (Thursday, May 29): Once per match, a single portal will appear in \u003cem\u003eFortnite\u003c/em\u003e. If you’re the first to the portal, you’ll be able to access the Star Destroyer’s control room — and its laser cannon.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Final Showdown: Death Star Sabotage\u003c/strong\u003e (Saturday, June 7): Epic Games didn’t share many details about “Death Star Sabotage”, but the event will be a narrative event that pits players against Emperor Palpatine.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eMay the Force be with you.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
